sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface	--> using tcpdump

sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface host ipaddress	--> using tcpdump for specific ipaddress
To test try pinging the ipaddress:

sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface dst medium.com -n  --> will show packets to medium.com
sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface net 192.168.0.0/24   --> will show packets to a subnet
sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface port 443 -vv  -n -->    --> will show packets to  https traffic

sudo tcpdump -i networkInterface dst port 53 -vv -n   --> will show traffic to or from particular port
Use -a to output packet in ascii
